{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A study of more than 100 large American corporations, which together employ 8 million people, suggests that writing is a more important skill for professionals today than it ever has been (College Entrance Examination Board, 2004, pp. 3-4). Two-thirds of professionals need strong writing skills in their daily work. Fifty percent of all companies in all industries consider writ\u173?ing skills in making promotion decisions. And almost half of the largest U.S. companies offer or require training for professionals who cannot write well (College Entrance Examination Board, 2004, p. 4). These companies spend, on average, $900 per employee for writing training. Would a company rather not have to spend that $900? Yes.\par}
